Samuel Ortom, governor of Benue, and his colleagues from Oyo and Rivers states, Seyi Makinde and Nyesom Wike, held a meeting with former President Olusegun Obasanjo on Monday. Donald Duke, former governor of Cross River, also attended the meeting. The meeting, which held behind closed doors, took place at the residence of the former president in Abeokuta, the Ogun capital. Speaking on the purpose of the meeting, Wike, presidential hopeful on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), said Obasanjo was consulted on national issues. See photos below. <img class="size-full wp-image-702806 alignnone" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220523-WA0012-1.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="374" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220523-WA0012-1.jpg 720w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220523-WA0012-1-300x156.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220523-WA0012-1-24x12.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220523-WA0012-1-36x19.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220523-WA0012-1-48x25.jpg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px" /> <img class="size-full wp-image-702805 alignnone" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220523-WA0011-1.jpg" alt="" width="717" height="400" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220523-WA0011-1.jpg 717w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220523-WA0011-1-300x167.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220523-WA0011-1-24x13.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220523-WA0011-1-36x20.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/IMG-20220523-WA0011-1-48x27.jpg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 717px) 100vw, 717px" /> <img class